element.name: Let's get Fizzical by Windsockers, Unknown Cache (5/5)

long-description.p: 1. The posted coordinates are the coordinates for the cache,However in order to log a find you will need to complete the full grid an example of which is shown in the image above. there are a total of 81 differant cache types needed to be found before you can log this cache.

2. Generally accepted rules, guidelines and conditions for logging a cache find apply. Caches must be listed on Gecaching.com you personally (physically) must have found and logged all the required caches.
3. Cache types that count as finds for the challenge are as follows:

- EarthCache
- Event Cache
- Letterbox Hybrid
- Cito Event
- Multi Cache
- Traditional Cache
- Unknown Cache
- Virtual Cache
- Webcam Cache

4. While you may have others with you when you find the final cache, only those who have fulfilled all criteria for this cache will be allowed to log it as a find. Find logs by other cachers that do not meet the requirements will be deleted.

5. Only the Difficulty/Terrain (Star) ratings as listed on cache pages will be accepted. I am only responsible for this cache page…if a cache owner changes a rating either up or down and causes a loss in one of the Difficulty/Terrain ratings before you find the cache, you will need to find an additional cache to complete that requirement. If a cache owner changes a rating up or down and causes a loss in one of the Difficulty/Terrain ratings after you find the cache, you are NOT expected to find an additional cache (but if you were dedicated enough to find all these ratings…could you really live with yourself if you didn’t try again.

6. How do you track your caches? There are three options: 1) Create a bookmark list and keep track 2) Upload your My Finds PQ to It's Not About The Numbers 3) Use FizzyMagic's FindStats Program (this requires a download)
7. When you have found all of the required combinations, post a note to this cache page and include a link to your shared bookmark list showing all the caches that meet the requirements.
8. Please use a shared bookmark list (and link) available to other cachers for a minimum of a few months after completing the challenge.

9. For nine of the caches on your bookmark list, include what type (i.e., Traditional, Virtual, EarthCache) of cache it is in the comments section for that cache. Make sure each of the nine required cache types are included. Please do not do this for every cache on the list.
10. A minimum of 81 caches are needed on your bookmark list to be eligible to log the final.
11. After you have posted your note with the needed shared bookmark list, please wait patiently for the cache owner to verify your list.
12. Once verification has shown that you have successfully completed the challenge you can then log the cache.
13. Remember that this is a game and is supposed to be fun.

The Difficulty/Terrain (Star) rating for this cache is set as a 5/5 to reflect the overall ratings for the caches that need to be found for this challange.
The actual rating is 1.5/2 at most. This cache cannot be used as the required 5/5 cache.
